[
  {
    "startTime": 6.92,
    "endTime": 8.48,
    "text": "Sam: Hello. This is 6 Minute English,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 8.48,
    "endTime": 9.14,
    "text": "I'm Sam."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 9.14,
    "endTime": 10.14,
    "text": "Neil: And I'm Neil."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 10.14,
    "endTime": 12.4,
    "text": "Sam: Do you like sad music, Neil?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 12.4,
    "endTime": 14.200000000000001,
    "text": "Neil: Well, when I was younger and if I had"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 14.2,
    "endTime": 16.219,
    "text": "a break-up with a girlfriend I would listen"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 16.219,
    "endTime": 18.0,
    "text": "to sad songs, songs which"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 18.0,
    "endTime": 19.62,
    "text": "reflected my mood."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 19.62,
    "endTime": 21.380000000000003,
    "text": "Sam: And do you still listen"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 21.38,
    "endTime": 22.46,
    "text": "to those songs now?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 22.46,
    "endTime": 24.201,
    "text": "Neil: Not so much, but I do still"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.201,
    "endTime": 25.150000000000002,
    "text": "like them."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 25.15,
    "endTime": 27.22,
    "text": "Sam: Well, it seems as if there might be"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 27.22,
    "endTime": 28.98,
    "text": "a biological reason why"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.983,
    "endTime": 30.34,
    "text": "some of us do like sad"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 30.34,
    "endTime": 32.778,
    "text": "songs. We'll look at this topic a little more"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 32.78,
    "endTime": 35.0,
    "text": "after this week's quiz question, which is"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 35.0,
    "endTime": 36.88,
    "text": "about music videos."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.88,
    "endTime": 38.752,
    "text": "The music video has been around"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 38.76,
    "endTime": 42.239,
    "text": "for a while, but in what year was MTV,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.24,
    "endTime": 44.480000000000004,
    "text": "the first dedicated music video"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 44.48,
    "endTime": 47.278999999999996,
    "text": "channel, launched in the US?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.28,
    "endTime": 51.84,
    "text": "Was it... A: 1981, B: 1982, or"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 51.84,
    "endTime": 54.400000000000006,
    "text": "C: 1983?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 54.4,
    "endTime": 55.44,
    "text": "Neil: Well..."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 55.44,
    "endTime": 56.94,
    "text": "Sam: What do you think, Neil?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.94,
    "endTime": 57.98,
    "text": "Neil: I'm going to guess."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.98,
    "endTime": 60.0,
    "text": "Is it the early 1980s?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 60.0,
    "endTime": 64.019,
    "text": "Sam: Well, yes. Care to be more specific?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 64.03,
    "endTime": 66.93,
    "text": "Neil: Well... Well, it was a long time ago"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 66.93,
    "endTime": 69.76,
    "text": "- I was just a small boy. I'm going to go"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 69.76,
    "endTime": 71.48,
    "text": "for 1982."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 71.48,
    "endTime": 73.29400000000001,
    "text": "Sam: OK, I'll have answer later"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 73.3,
    "endTime": 75.14,
    "text": "in the programme. But first,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 75.14,
    "endTime": 77.88,
    "text": "more about sad songs. Professor"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 77.88,
    "endTime": 80.78,
    "text": "David Huron from Ohio State University"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.78,
    "endTime": 82.16,
    "text": "has conducted research"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 82.16,
    "endTime": 83.6,
    "text": "in this area and he discussed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 83.6,
    "endTime": 85.809,
    "text": "it recently on a BBC World Service"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 85.81,
    "endTime": 87.991,
    "text": "radio programme - The Why Factor."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 87.991,
    "endTime": 89.71,
    "text": "He was looking at why some"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.71,
    "endTime": 91.54499999999999,
    "text": "people like sad music and"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 91.546,
    "endTime": 94.381,
    "text": "other people really don't like it all,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 94.381,
    "endTime": 96.32,
    "text": "as he says they just can't"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 96.32,
    "endTime": 98.648,
    "text": "stand it. He believes it's to do"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 98.649,
    "endTime": 100.721,
    "text": "with a hormone. A hormone is"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 100.721,
    "endTime": 103.09,
    "text": "a natural chemical in our bodies"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 103.09,
    "endTime": 104.86,
    "text": "which can have an effect on various"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 104.86,
    "endTime": 106.96,
    "text": "systems and also emotions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 106.96,
    "endTime": 108.559,
    "text": "Listen out for the name"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 108.56,
    "endTime": 110.18,
    "text": "of the hormone he mentions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 111.3,
    "endTime": 112.179,
    "text": "Professor Huron: One of the things"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.18,
    "endTime": 112.95500000000001,
    "text": "that we were interested in was -"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.955,
    "endTime": 113.85,
    "text": "what's the difference"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 113.85,
    "endTime": 114.979,
    "text": "between people who listen"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 114.98,
    "endTime": 116.8,
    "text": "to sad music and who love it,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 116.8,
    "endTime": 118.33,
    "text": "and people who listen to sad"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 118.33,
    "endTime": 120.0,
    "text": "music and who just can't stand it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 120.0,
    "endTime": 122.634,
    "text": "In our research, it started pointing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 122.635,
    "endTime": 123.69000000000001,
    "text": "towards a hormone"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 123.69,
    "endTime": 125.431,
    "text": "called prolactin. Now, prolactin,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 125.44,
    "endTime": 127.12,
    "text": "as you might have guessed from the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 127.12,
    "endTime": 128.28,
    "text": "name, is associated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.28,
    "endTime": 130.64000000000001,
    "text": "with 'lactation' from breast-feeding."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 130.639,
    "endTime": 133.279,
    "text": "When people cry, they also"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 133.28,
    "endTime": 135.099,
    "text": "release prolactin. And,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.099,
    "endTime": 137.153,
    "text": "there are circumstances in which"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 137.16,
    "endTime": 138.48,
    "text": "prolactin seems to have"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 138.48,
    "endTime": 140.16,
    "text": "this comforting effect."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 141.1,
    "endTime": 143.32,
    "text": "Sam: So which hormone did he mention?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 143.32,
    "endTime": 144.85899999999998,
    "text": "Neil: He talked about the hormone"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 144.86,
    "endTime": 146.88000000000002,
    "text": "called prolactin which he said was"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 146.88,
    "endTime": 148.66,
    "text": "connected to lactation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 148.66,
    "endTime": 150.76,
    "text": "This is the production of milk by"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 150.76,
    "endTime": 152.399,
    "text": "mammals to feed their young."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.4,
    "endTime": 154.467,
    "text": "Sam: What he noted was this"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 154.467,
    "endTime": 156.769,
    "text": "hormone can be released when people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 156.769,
    "endTime": 158.15,
    "text": "cry and in some cases"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 158.15,
    "endTime": 160.52800000000002,
    "text": "this hormone has a comforting effect."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 160.528,
    "endTime": 162.433,
    "text": "When something is comforting,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 162.433,
    "endTime": 163.549,
    "text": "it makes you feel"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 163.549,
    "endTime": 166.116,
    "text": "better, it calms your emotions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.12,
    "endTime": 167.68,
    "text": "Let's listen again."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 168.48,
    "endTime": 169.34,
    "text": "Professor Huron: One of the things"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 169.34,
    "endTime": 170.08,
    "text": "that we were interested in was -"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.081,
    "endTime": 170.849,
    "text": "what's the difference"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.849,
    "endTime": 172.06,
    "text": "between people who listen"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 172.06,
    "endTime": 173.78,
    "text": "to sad music and who love it,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.784,
    "endTime": 175.319,
    "text": "and people who listen to sad"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 175.319,
    "endTime": 177.393,
    "text": "music and who just can't stand it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 177.394,
    "endTime": 179.632,
    "text": "In our research, it started pointing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 179.632,
    "endTime": 180.0,
    "text": "towards a hormone"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 180.0,
    "endTime": 182.426,
    "text": "called prolactin. Now, prolactin,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 182.426,
    "endTime": 184.035,
    "text": "as you might have guessed from"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.035,
    "endTime": 185.269,
    "text": "the name, is associated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 185.269,
    "endTime": 187.68,
    "text": "with 'lactation' from breast-feeding."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 187.68,
    "endTime": 190.26000000000002,
    "text": "When people cry, they also"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 190.26,
    "endTime": 192.099,
    "text": "release prolactin. And,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 192.099,
    "endTime": 194.027,
    "text": "there are circumstances in which"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 194.027,
    "endTime": 195.44199999999998,
    "text": "prolactin seems to have"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 195.443,
    "endTime": 197.04000000000002,
    "text": "this comforting effect."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 197.92,
    "endTime": 199.51899999999998,
    "text": "Sam: So, what conclusions did he make"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 199.524,
    "endTime": 201.437,
    "text": "about this hormone and how"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 201.437,
    "endTime": 202.90900000000002,
    "text": "it might be working?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 202.909,
    "endTime": 204.519,
    "text": "Professor Huron explains."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 205.6,
    "endTime": 206.78,
    "text": "Professor Huron: So the thought was that,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 206.8,
    "endTime": 208.091,
    "text": "perhaps what's going on"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 208.091,
    "endTime": 209.109,
    "text": "is that the people"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 209.109,
    "endTime": 211.585,
    "text": "who are enjoying listening to sad music"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.585,
    "endTime": 212.74,
    "text": "are receiving some sort"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 212.74,
    "endTime": 214.56,
    "text": "of excess of prolactin,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 214.56,
    "endTime": 216.02,
    "text": "and people who are listening to sad"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 216.02,
    "endTime": 217.9,
    "text": "music and they just find it"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 217.9,
    "endTime": 219.4,
    "text": "incredibly sad and unhelpful"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 219.4,
    "endTime": 220.5,
    "text": "and they just don't want to listen to it,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 220.5,
    "endTime": 221.68,
    "text": "maybe they're not getting"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.68,
    "endTime": 222.9,
    "text": "enough prolactin"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 222.9,
    "endTime": 224.24,
    "text": "when they listen to the music."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 225.16,
    "endTime": 226.579,
    "text": "Sam: So what is happening?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 226.588,
    "endTime": 228.542,
    "text": "Or as Professor Huron said,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 228.542,
    "endTime": 229.7,
    "text": "what's going on?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 229.7,
    "endTime": 232.155,
    "text": "Neil: Well, it seems quite simple, though"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 232.155,
    "endTime": 234.67,
    "text": "I'm sure it's very complicated. People who"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 234.67,
    "endTime": 236.75,
    "text": "like sad music are maybe getting"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 236.75,
    "endTime": 238.47,
    "text": "too much prolactin or more"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 238.47,
    "endTime": 240.0,
    "text": "than is normal - he describes"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 240.0,
    "endTime": 242.36,
    "text": "this as an excess of prolactin."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 242.38,
    "endTime": 244.4,
    "text": "And maybe people who don't like"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 244.4,
    "endTime": 246.8,
    "text": "sad music aren't getting enough."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 246.8,
    "endTime": 249.26000000000002,
    "text": "Sam: So, the idea is that prolactin"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 249.26,
    "endTime": 251.797,
    "text": "is a hormone which we find comforting."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 251.797,
    "endTime": 253.2,
    "text": "If our bodies release"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 253.209,
    "endTime": 255.758,
    "text": "it when we hear sad music, it gives us a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 255.76,
    "endTime": 257.777,
    "text": "good feeling - but if prolactin"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 257.779,
    "endTime": 259.479,
    "text": "isn't released or there isn't"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 259.48,
    "endTime": 261.84000000000003,
    "text": "enough of it, we just find the sad music"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 261.839,
    "endTime": 264.76,
    "text": "sad and it doesn't help to cheer us up."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 265.1,
    "endTime": 266.12,
    "text": "Neil: I guess so, but you know"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 266.12,
    "endTime": 267.899,
    "text": "emotions are funny things - it's"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 267.899,
    "endTime": 268.849,
    "text": "weird to think that our"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 268.849,
    "endTime": 270.878,
    "text": "feelings are caused by different"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 270.88,
    "endTime": 272.6,
    "text": "natural chemicals that run around"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 272.6,
    "endTime": 273.358,
    "text": "the body."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 273.36,
    "endTime": 275.02000000000004,
    "text": "Sam: Absolutely! OK,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 275.02,
    "endTime": 276.452,
    "text": "we're going to take another look at"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 276.46,
    "endTime": 278.58,
    "text": "today's vocabulary but first, the answer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 278.58,
    "endTime": 280.3,
    "text": "to this week's quiz."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 280.3,
    "endTime": 281.84000000000003,
    "text": "The music video has been around"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 281.86,
    "endTime": 283.92,
    "text": "for a while, but in what year"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 283.92,
    "endTime": 285.76,
    "text": "was MTV, the first"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 285.76,
    "endTime": 288.52,
    "text": "dedicated music video channel, launched"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 288.52,
    "endTime": 293.02,
    "text": "in the US? Was it... A: 1981, B: 1982"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 293.02,
    "endTime": 294.88,
    "text": "or C: 1983?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 294.88,
    "endTime": 296.64,
    "text": "And Neil, you said..."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 296.64,
    "endTime": 299.719,
    "text": "Neil: I said it was definitely the early 80s."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 299.72,
    "endTime": 301.86,
    "text": "Sam: Well, you're not wrong there,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 301.88,
    "endTime": 303.439,
    "text": "but which year exactly?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 303.44,
    "endTime": 305.34,
    "text": "Neil: '82?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 305.34,
    "endTime": 307.84,
    "text": "Sam: Ah well, you'll need to dig out"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 307.84,
    "endTime": 309.513,
    "text": "a sad song to make you feel better"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 309.52,
    "endTime": 310.568,
    "text": "now because the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 310.569,
    "endTime": 312.6,
    "text": "answer was 1981."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 312.6,
    "endTime": 314.5,
    "text": "Neil: Oh dear, I can feel my"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 314.5,
    "endTime": 316.25,
    "text": "prolactin levels dropping already!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 316.25,
    "endTime": 319.146,
    "text": "Sam: I'm sure you can't! But let's move on"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 319.146,
    "endTime": 320.62800000000004,
    "text": "to vocabulary. If you"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 320.628,
    "endTime": 322.18,
    "text": "can't stand something,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 322.18,
    "endTime": 323.77,
    "text": "it means you really don't like it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 323.77,
    "endTime": 325.316,
    "text": "Neil: A hormone is one of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 325.316,
    "endTime": 327.109,
    "text": "the body's natural chemicals."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 327.11,
    "endTime": 328.878,
    "text": "Sam: And the hormone prolactin"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 328.878,
    "endTime": 330.558,
    "text": "is connected with lactation,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 330.559,
    "endTime": 332.12,
    "text": "which is the production of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 332.12,
    "endTime": 333.31,
    "text": "milk by mammals."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 333.31,
    "endTime": 335.16,
    "text": "Neil: Something that is comforting"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 335.18,
    "endTime": 337.42,
    "text": "makes you feel better emotionally."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 337.42,
    "endTime": 339.34000000000003,
    "text": "Sam: The phrase 'what's going on' has"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 339.349,
    "endTime": 341.037,
    "text": "a very similar meaning to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 341.037,
    "endTime": 342.318,
    "text": "'what's happening'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 342.319,
    "endTime": 344.329,
    "text": "Neil: And an excess of something is"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 344.329,
    "endTime": 346.14300000000003,
    "text": "'too much or a more than normal"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 346.143,
    "endTime": 347.429,
    "text": "amount of that thing'."
